  "texts": [
    "Several studies have employed CNN architectures for fossil segmentation.",
    "Panigrahi et al. (2023) present Model Editing techniques with DL models to segment ancient reef fossils from rock sample images.",
    "Model editing techniques involve modifying a pre-trained model to improve its performance or adapt it to new tasks without extensive retraining.",
    "Specifically, a Mask R-CNN is fine-tuned by identifying its weaknesses using image perturbations and mitigating them using model editing.",
    "This research relies on a model trained on a limited number of images from only one rock sample, however, and as such the possible generalization of the model to other datasets may be challenging."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Panigrahi et al. (2023) present Model Editing techniques with DL models to segment ancient reef fossils from rock sample images."
  ]
